his Act may be cited as the\n\t\t\t ", "@display-inline": "no-display-inline"}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n      ", "#text": "1."}, "header": {"#tail": "\n      ", "#text": "Short title"}, "#text": "\n      ", "@id": "H2422609289ED42898A5297CA155C0568"}, {"#tail": "\n  ", "enum": {"#tail": "\n      ", "#text": "2."}, "header": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t", "#text": "Attorney\n\t\t\t accountability"}, "subsection": [{"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t\t", "#text": "Rule 11(c) of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure is\n\t\t\t amended\u2014"}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(a)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "Sanctions under\n\t\t\t rule 11"}, "paragraph": [{"#tail": "\n        ", "text": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t\t", "quote": [{"#tail": " and inserting ", "#text": "may"}, {"#tail": ";", "#text": "shall"}], "#text": "in paragraph (1),\n\t\t\t by striking "}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(1)"}, "@id": "H78C184D03CCA45B39BB8A261B847D41C", "#text": "\n          "}, {"#tail": "\n        ", "text": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t\t", "quote": [{"#tail": " and all that follows through\n\t\t\t ", "#text": "Rule 5"}, {"#tail": " and inserting ", "#text": "motion."}, {"#tail": "; and", "#text": "Rule 5."}], "#text": "in paragraph (2),\n\t\t\t by striking "}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(2)"}, "@id": "H4D6D5C9BD56F4064B9023AE10DB4A02A", "#text": "\n          "}, {"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t\t", "quote": [{"#tail": " and all that follows through the end of the\n\t\t\t paragraph and inserting ", "#text": "situated"}, {"#tail": ".", "#text": "situated, and to compensate the parties that\n\t\t\t were injured by such conduct. Subject to the limitations in paragraph (5), the\n\t\t\t sanction shall consist of an order to pay to the party or parties the amount of\n\t\t\t the reasonable expenses incurred as a direct result of the violation, including\n\t\t\t reasonable attorneys\u2019 fees and costs. The court may also impose additional\n\t\t\t appropriate sanctions, such as striking the pleadings, dismissing the suit, or\n\t\t\t other directives of a nonmonetary nature, or, if warranted for effective\n\t\t\t deterrence, an order directing payment of a penalty into the\n\t\t\t court."}], "#text": "in paragraph (4),\n\t\t\t by striking "}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(3)"}, "@id": "H6DD50F3C2F3A4F8D9ACFAF26AA9E5370", "#text": "\n          "}], "#text": "\n        ", "@id": "H9E15F99603C741DA868DAD6C51354EE7"}, {"#tail": "\n    ", "text": {"#tail": "\n\t\t\t", "#text": "Nothing in this\n\t\t\t Act or an amendment made by this Act shall be construed to bar or impede the\n\t\t\t assertion or development of new claims, defenses, or remedies under Federal,\n\t\t\t State, or local laws, including civil rights laws, or under the Constitution of\n\t\t\t the United States.", "@display-inline": "yes-display-inline"}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(b)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "Rule of\n\t\t\t construction"}, "#text": "\n        ", "@id": "H7B004F958A054A28B831B3E49B8BC298"}], "#text": "\n      ", "@id": "H0063719F9F69443A941151AF26FE5BB6"}], "#text": "\n\t\t", "@id": "HC017AC409470482E87B12E28E8BBED48"}, "metadata": {"#tail": "\n", "dublinCore": {"{http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/}date": {"#tail": "\n", "#text": "2013-07-11"}, "{http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/}format": {"#tail": "\n", "#text": "text/xml"}, "{http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/}language": {"#tail": "\n", "#text": "EN"}, "#tail": "\n", "{http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/}title": {"#tail": "\n", "#text": "113 HR 2655 IH: Lawsuit Abuse Reduction Act of 2013"}, "{http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/}rights": {"#tail": "\n", "#text": "Pursuant to Title 17 Section 105 of the United States Code, this file is not subject to copyright protection and is in the public domain."}, "{http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/}publisher": {"#tail": "\n", "#text": "U.S. House of Representatives"}, "#text": "\n"}, "#tex